  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition" corresp="#Ed">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="KT320-kilavi">alar añci āṟṟāḷākiya talaimakaḷ talaimakaṉ kēṭpāṉākat tōḻikkuk kūṟiyatu. </p>
        <p xml:lang="en">Spoken to the confidante, while HE listens, by HER, who
          doesn't have strength [anymore] because of the gossip. </p>
      </div>

      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="KT320">
          <l> peruṅkaṭaṟ paratavar koṇmī ṉuṇaṅkali</l>
          <l> ṉaruṅkaḻik koṇṭa viṟaviṉ vāṭaloṭu</l>
          <l> nilavuniṟa veṇmaṇal pulavap palavuṭa</l>
          <l> ṉekkartoṟum parikkun tuṟaivaṉō ṭorunā</l>
          <l> ṇakkatōr paḻiyu milamē pōtaviḻ</l>
          <l> poṉṉiṇar marīiya puḷḷimiḻ poṅkarp</l>
          <l> puṉṉaiyañ cēri yivvūr</l>
          <l> koṉṉalar tūṟṟuntaṉ koṭumai yāṉē.</l>
        </lg>

        <lg xml:lang="en">
          <l>We are without any blame <note place="foot"> <term xml:lang="ta"> ōr paḻi-yum </term>: has the <term xml:lang="ta"> -um </term> to be read as a marking of the indefinite?  </note> of having laughed a single day</l>
          <l rend="indent">with the man from the ghat, where they spread over every dune</l>
          <l rend="indent2">drying [bits] of fish caught by the fishermen of the great sea,</l>
          <l rend="indent3">together with fading prawns from the difficult <note place="foot"> <term xml:lang="ta"> arum kaḻi </term> does not make much sense. Lectio facilior is definitely the formulaic <term xml:lang="ta"> irum kaḻi </term>, adopted into the text by <term xml:lang="ta"> Vaiyāpurip Piḷḷai </term> and <term xml:lang="ta"> Caṉmukam Piḷḷai </term> 1985, but attested only as a variant in a single manuscript.     </note> backwaters,</l>
          <l rend="indent5">many together,</l>
          <l rend="indent4">so that the moonlight-coloured sand reeks [of them].</l>
          <l>This village of streets [planted] with Puṉṉai,</l>
          <l rend="indent">[their] branches buzzing with birds joined <note place="foot"> <term xml:lang="ta"> marīiya </term>: are the clusters joined with the birds or with the branches?   </note> with golden clusters</l>
          <l rend="indent9">of opening buds,</l>
          <l>vainly spreads gossip in its cruelty.</l>

          <lg type="alternate" sameAs="8b">
            <l>vainly spreads gossip about his cruelty.</l>
          </lg>
        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
